    "narrative": "For Ghost Ride the WHIP on this April 16th, our offensive strategy hinges on exploiting favorable matchups against struggling arms. **Tyler Soderstrom** leads the charge with a 76.91 score, bolstered by a 10% park factor bump and a high-leverage cleanup spot against Leiter. Following closely are **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.75), both of whom benefit from significant platoon advantages and the soft target of Ryan Weiss (7.36 xERA). **Josh Naylor** (74.81) remains a locked-in start, as his 19% SP skill boost against Walker Buehler outweighs the risk of a right-on-right matchup. We are also tracking **Brice Turang** closely; while his base projection is modest, his potential for stolen bases against a slow-delivering pitcher makes his 64.27 score an essential component of our pursuit of the SB category.\n\nOur most delicate lineup decision centered on the middle infield and catcher slots. **Jose Caballero** edged out the marginal tiers with a 63.52 score, largely due to a 13% boost from his favorable platoon matchup against Suter. Conversely, **Luis Campusano** is sitting at a 43.78, barely holding his spot as a marginal play; he remains in the lineup only because of our limited options, though we are monitoring his status closely should his confirmed batting order slip further. **Kyle Karros** (50.77) and **James Wood** (55.43) are the most volatile starters today\u2014**James Wood** in particular is being hampered by a negative SP skill adjustment and a low ceiling against a pitcher who effectively controls the running game. With **Corbin Carroll**, **Austin Riley**, **Seiya Suzuki**, and **Trevor Story** all inactive, we have no bench depth to rotate in should the late-afternoon lineups for **Luis Campusano** or **Kyle Karros** shift negatively. We will rely on our depth, including **Gabriel Moreno**, **Max Muncy**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Alex Freeland**, **Carson Williams**, and **Travis Bazzana**, to provide the necessary flexibility if any of today\u2019s projected lineups collapse before first pitch.",
